  "text": "The difficulty in the above argument lies in the \"right choice of parameters\". One of the limitations of Lemma 2.2 is that the number of vertices in the embedded graph should not be too large. In other words, the regularity measure required for Lemma 2.2 depends on the size f of F . This seems to be impossible, since F might be infinite. For that purpose we make our last two definitions, which follow the main idea behind the use of Lemma 2.7 in [CITATION_1] . Definition 3.7. For any (possibly infinite) family of graphs F, and any integer k, let F k be the following set of colored regularity graphs: A colored regularity graph K belongs to F k if it has at most k vertices and there is at least one F ∈ F such that F → c K.",
